UID:10005143-1783443600-1783450800@iondistrict.com
SUMMARY:What AI\, Cybersecurity\, and Tequila Have in Common.
DESCRIPTION:Register here: https://luma.com/0rfy7te0 \nMost companies treat AI like a shortcut to growth: it delivers immediate results\, but the long-term operational fallout is brutal. \n​Everyone is caught up in the rush\, plugging automated tools into critical infrastructure without checking the foundation. But speed without security isn’t progress\, it’s an open invitation for cyber threats. It’s time to face the structural reality. \n​Join Blue People and Alpfa Houston for an unfiltered session with Reynaldo Gonzalez\, an industry veteran with 18+ years of experience securing critical infrastructure. \n​The Realities We’re Breaking Down: \n​AI doesn’t change the value of knowledge; it changes the value of curiosity. The ultimate security edge belongs to leaders who know how to ask the right questions\, not just trust the output. \n​Your biggest competitive advantage is becoming more human\, not less. In a world of automated systems\, human judgment and sharp intuition remain the only truly un-hackable firewalls left. \n​AI is the greatest operational amplifier ever created. It scales your wins\, but it weaponizes your internal flaws. If your baseline security is weak\, AI just helps you fail faster and at scale. \n​The single biggest risk today isn’t AI\, it’s human complacency. The danger isn’t rogue technology or advanced malware; it’s our own blind trust in automated workflows. \n​Stop operating on hope. Turn cyber resilience into your unfair advantage. \n​📅 July 7th\, 2026 | 5:00 PM – 7:00 PM\n📍 The Ion Houston\nHosted by Blue People & Alpfa Houston \n​👉 Ask about our parking options at the end of the event!
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/what-ai-cybersecurity-and-tequila-have-in-common/
LOCATION:Ion\, 4201 Main Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://iondistrict.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/IG-and-Linked-in-Post-1080x1350-24.png
END:VEVENT
